As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 749 people, 289 households, and 183 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=S1101 HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES - 2020: Jennings town, Florida|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Jennings+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1101|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 878 people, 275 households, and 213 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=S1101 HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES - 2010: Jennings town, Florida|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Jennings+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 833 people, 282 households, and 205 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|461.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 321 housing units at an average density of {{convert|177.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  The racial makeup of the town was 43.70% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 43.10% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.60% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.60% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 10.08% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.92% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 22.69% of the population.

[[File:Jennings city limit, CR143NB.JPG|thumb|200px|left|Jennings city limit sign]]
In 2000, there were 282 households out of which 33.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 44.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 20.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 27.3% were non-families. 23.0% of all households were made up of individuals and 11.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.89 and the average family size was 3.34.

In 2000, in the town, the population was spread out with 30.6% under the age of 18, 9.0% from 18 to 24, 25.7% from 25 to 44, 22.4% from 45 to 64, and 12.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 32 years. For every 100 females, there were 98.8 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 99.3 males.
[[File:Jennings FL High School pano01.jpg|thumb|200px|[[North Hamilton Elementary School]] (now closed)]]
[[File:Jennings library.jpg|thumb|200px|Jennings Public Library]]

In 2000, the median income for a household in the town was $25,714, and the median income for a family was $25,938. Males had a median income of $25,577 versus $15,982 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $12,195. About 23.8% of families and 30.8% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 42.9% of those under age 18 and 20.0% of those age 65 or over.

